<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Y. Ma, J. Wen, Q. Fu &amp; X. Q. Liu" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Vitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vitis shizishanensis" order="Vitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="shizishanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Vitis shizishanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bryoniifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bryoniifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bryoniifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bunge, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. flexuosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thunb, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. sinocinerea" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sinocinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. sinocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W. T. Wang, and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bellula" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Rehder) W. T. Wang, but differs from the 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bryoniifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bryoniifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bryoniifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. sinocinerea" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sinocinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. sinocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bellula" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its glabrous to hirtellously pubescent abaxial mature leaf surface (vs. abaxially densely arachnoid tomentose in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bryoniifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bryoniifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bryoniifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. sinocinerea" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="sinocinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. sinocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. bellula" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Vitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vitis flexuosa" order="Vitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Vitis flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its leaves varying from unlobed to 3-7 lobed (vs. unlobed to slightly 3-lobed leaves in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. flexuosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), tendrils unbranched or bifurcate from upper half (vs. tendrils bifurcate from approximately midway in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. flexuosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lack of arachnoid tomentum (vs. with sparse arachnoid tomentum to glabrescent in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. flexuosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and subcordate to cordate or sometimes truncate leaf base (vs. subtruncate or slightly subcordate leaf base in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. flexuosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">V. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
